# data-models-relationships

Key Data Models and Relationships:

1. Youth Profile Model
Importance Score: 95
- Core profile entity with specialized behavioral health attributes
- Relationships:
  * One-to-many with DailyPerformanceNotes 
  * One-to-many with BehaviorIncidents
  * One-to-many with AcademicRecords
  * One-to-many with BehavioralAssessment
  * Many-to-many with TreatmentGoals
  * One-to-one with MedicalProfile
- Domain-specific fields:
  * Treatment level (1-6)
  * Current restrictions
  * Behavioral point totals
  * Active interventions
  * Guardian relationships

2. Daily Performance Notes Schema
Importance Score: 90
- Structured behavioral tracking across 4 domains
- Relationships:
  * Many-to-one with Youth
  * One-to-many with BehaviorIncidents
  * One-to-many with StaffAnnotations
- Behavioral metrics:
  * Peer interaction rating (1-4)
  * Adult interaction rating (1-4)
  * Investment level (1-4)
  * Authority response (1-4)

3. Medical Profile Schema 
Importance Score: 85
- Healthcare-specific youth data model
- Relationships:
  * One-to-one with Youth
  * One-to-many with Medications
  * One-to-many with MedicalAlerts
- Clinical tracking:
  * Current medications
  * Dosage schedules
  * Allergies/restrictions
  * Medical conditions
  * Treatment authorizations

4. TreatmentGoals Model
Importance Score: 80
- Treatment planning and goal tracking
- Relationships:
  * Many-to-many with Youth
  * One-to-many with Interventions
  * Many-to-many with BehavioralMetrics
- Focus categories:
  * Behavioral objectives
  * Social skill development
  * Academic goals
  * Family integration
  * Life skills mastery

5. Behavioral Assessment Schema
Importance Score: 75
- Point-based behavior tracking system
- Relationships:
  * Many-to-one with Youth
  * One-to-many with BehaviorIncidents
  * One-to-many with StaffNotes
- Assessment metrics:
  * Daily point totals
  * Rolling averages
  * Level progression data
  * Restriction tracking

Core Entity Relationships:
- Youth as central entity
- Treatment goals linked to behavioral metrics
- Medical profiles with medication tracking
- Daily notes connected to incidents
- Assessment data tied to interventions

